news.title: Web portal launched to help citizens rectify land records in Jharkhand
news.para: Director of land acquisition and land archives, Jharkhand, Uma Shankar Singh told TOI that many could not benefit from the schemes under Jharbhoomi, a portal for online land registration, due to documentation errors.

news.title: Mysuru city corporation collects record property tax in two weeks
news.para: In the last two and half weeks, although there were extended weekends and festival holidays, Mysuru City Corporation collected Rs 21 crore in taxes — more than nearly 40% — mostly residential.

news.title: Over 13,700 applications for 415 plots near Jewar airport
news.para: ​​The authority had included in the draw plots ranging from 300 to 4,000 sq metres across sectors 16, 17, 18, 20 and 22D.

news.title: Patna HC directs ED to register case against builder
news.para: A single bench of Justice Sandeep Kumar, while hearing an anticipatory bail plea of one Prabhat Kumar Ranjan, directed the Enforcement Directorate (ED) as well as director (investigation) of Income Tax department to furnish their action taken reports (ATRs) by the next date of hearing.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: 19,000 illegal layouts put on hold by planning department
news.para: The layouts were declared 'unauthorised' since they were laid without clearances. The transactions of plots in the 19,000 layouts spread over urban and rural areas were stalled. Sources said that over 1 lakh acres are involved in these layouts.

news.title: Outages frequent, builder yet to set up infra: Tata Gurgaon Gateway residents
news.para: According to the residents, an 11 KV feeder line from a substation near Palam Vihar supplies power to their flats. This is because the developer is yet to build a 33kV switching station.

news.title: SC refuses to examine plea on deciding stamp duty on carpet area
news.para: A bench of Justices U U Lalit and Bela M Trivedi said that it would be better if the issue is examined by competent authority as the apex court's decision would become final and the parties would not have the option to appeal.

news.title: Mumbai: Lodha Developers gets clean chit from GST anti-profiteering body
news.para: In this case, Darshan Joshi, an apartment buyer, had complained that Lodha Developers had resorted to profiteering by not passing on the commensurate GST-related benefits via a reduction in the prices of the apartments. He claimed he had lost out on Rs 1.8 lakh.

news.title: Blackstone's Nucleus Office Parks ups 2022 leasing guidance on office demand rebound
news.para: In the last two quarters, the company has leased over 5.3 million sq ft space including renewals across its office parks in key property markets of the country. Based on the demand and enquiry levels, Nucleus Office Parks expects to convert demand of at least 3 million sq ft this year.

news.title: SC directs banks not to declare accounts of Amrapali flat buyers as NPA, no penalty for default
news.para: A Subvention Scheme in the present case is a legal agreement made between the home buyer, the developer Amrapali Group of Companies, and the banks providing the home loan.

news.title: Draw of lots for DDA Special Housing Scheme, 2021 conducted successfully
news.para: "DDA initially placed 18,335 flats located in 28 localities under the scheme. In response to it, only 12,387 applicants have deposited requisite registration fee, although around 22,100 got themselves registered.

news.title: Kerala government recalls officials sent to Idukki to verify title deeds
news.para: According to sources, the government has asked Idukki collector to relieve 10 revenue officials of the 30 officials who were drawn from various districts and deputed to Idukki to assist the Idukki district administration for cancelling the existing titles and completing the procedures for issuing fresh titles to the holders of 532 land titles.

news.title: SC asks states to respond to queries of centre on implementation of RERA rules
news.para: A bench of Justices DY Chandrachud and Surya Kant said that in March 2022 the Centre has written to all the States seeking certain information with regard to the agreement of sales rules notified under the RERA Act and their compliance but only five States have so far responded to it.

news.title: Puravankara sales bookings rise 9% to record Rs 2,406 crore in FY 2022
news.para: In terms of volume, the sales bookings of Puravankara Ltd increased to 3.52 million square feet in 2021-22 fiscal, from 3.43 million square feet in the 2020-21 financial year.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace buys 11.5 acres of land in Pune
news.para: "The land is estimated to have a developable potential of approximately 2 million square feet of saleable area and a Gross Development Value of around Rs 1,700 crore," it said in a regulatory filing.
